<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<section xml:id="accommodations" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title> Accommodations</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
        If you have a documented disability requiring an accommodation, please contact the O'Neill Center for Student Access and Support, 
        located in M. M. Wilkens Hall (South) building room 222 or call 774-330-4337. Accommodations will not be provided without a College 
        Accommodation Plan from the O'Neill Center for Student Access and Support. It is the responsibility of a student who has a College 
        Accommodation Plan to set up an appointment to meet with their instructor, as early as possible in the semester, to discuss their 
        plan.
    </p>
  </introduction>
</section>